1
00:01:30,830 --> 00:01:34,990
[Dream of Golden Years]

2
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:39,070
[2006]

3
00:01:46,380 --> 00:01:51,560
[I went to your home and learned that you'd
gone to Shengcheng to earn tuition fees.]

4
00:01:51,580 --> 00:01:57,610
[You must finish your college anyway.
Don't ever give up on yourself.]

5
00:01:57,630 --> 00:02:04,010
[Please believe the sea's vast for fish
to leap; the sky's wide for birds to fly.]

6
00:02:05,310 --> 00:02:07,510
Wash faster! We're waiting to use them!

7
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:17,430
As I wanted to escape the past

8
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:18,560
and start fresh,

9
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:22,079
many people and things

10
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:24,640
turned into unspeakable secrets.

11
00:02:25,050 --> 00:02:28,900
[Episode 26 Unspeakable Secrets]

12
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:31,800
The work isn't tiring.

13
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:32,360
The Boss is here.

14
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:32,890
Hi, Boss.

15
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:34,440
Hurry up and eat.

16
00:02:34,470 --> 00:02:36,190
Get back to work as soon as you're done.

17
00:02:36,190 --> 00:02:36,990
Do you hear me?

18
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,840
Eat up, eat up. Stop looking.

19
00:02:41,079 --> 00:02:42,030
Big Brother, welcome.

20
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:42,590
Have you eaten?

21
00:02:42,590 --> 00:02:43,520
Do you want some?

22
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:44,280
I just ate.

23
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,210
Please sit down.

24
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:47,880
Everything is ready.

25
00:02:47,910 --> 00:02:48,710
It's all good.

26
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,310
Carry on.

27
00:02:49,310 --> 00:02:49,630
Take a seat.

28
00:02:49,630 --> 00:02:50,280
Go on with your work.

29
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,480
Okay, I'll get going.

30
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:54,290
I want more, please. A bit more.

31
00:02:54,750 --> 00:02:55,400
This rice.

32
00:02:56,590 --> 00:02:58,680
Shengcheng, as a window

33
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:00,000
for the Reform and Opening-Up,

34
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,400
bears the important position

35
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,930
of a pioneer in this policy.

36
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:04,450
In the coming years,

37
00:03:04,450 --> 00:03:06,100
it will develop rapidly

38
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,560
into a modern,

39
00:03:07,630 --> 00:03:09,230
international metropolis.

40
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:11,950
What are you looking at? Serve the food!

41
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:12,710
To stand out,

42
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,680
we need a special highlight.

43
00:03:15,610 --> 00:03:17,490
The infinity pool mentioned

44
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,870
in my design proposal

45
00:03:19,079 --> 00:03:19,960
will make it...

46
00:03:19,980 --> 00:03:20,800
Look at her.

47
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:22,730
You're both named Xia.

48
00:03:23,079 --> 00:03:24,030
But look at you!

49
00:03:26,630 --> 00:03:27,190
What?

50
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,930
You got a problem with that?

51
00:03:29,030 --> 00:03:30,430
If I didn't give you a job,

52
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:31,470
that big family of yours

53
00:03:31,470 --> 00:03:33,630
would've starved to death long ago,
you know?

54
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:35,090
Hurry up and keep working!

55
00:03:37,630 --> 00:03:39,430
These are all my ideas

56
00:03:39,450 --> 00:03:40,380
about my design.

57
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:43,350
Gong Yang.

58
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:44,870
Ms. Xia.

59
00:03:45,590 --> 00:03:47,360
Take this file back and review it.

60
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:47,710
Okay.

61
00:03:48,079 --> 00:03:48,960
Goodbye, Ms. Xia.

62
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:49,490
Bye-bye.

63
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,150
Ms. Xia.

64
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,430
Were you looking

65
00:04:03,430 --> 00:04:04,750
at that girl in blue?

66
00:04:06,710 --> 00:04:08,630
She's been hanging around
all the time lately,

67
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:10,400
never coming in or looking for anyone.

68
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,860
Should we call the police?

69
00:04:11,910 --> 00:04:13,170
It's fine. Ignore her.

70
00:04:16,269 --> 00:04:17,370
Isn't that the woman

71
00:04:17,370 --> 00:04:19,170
who used to sell clothes at Luna?

72
00:04:19,870 --> 00:04:21,000
Now she's following Xia Xiaolan

73
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,400
to construct buildings?

74
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:24,970
She'd rather help an outsider

75
00:04:24,970 --> 00:04:26,480
than her own cousin.

76
00:04:27,070 --> 00:04:28,530
She sides with outsiders.

77
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:31,920
We received the mortgage loan
from the bank

78
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,560
the other day when you were
in Jiangcheng.

79
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,390
Manager Ge

80
00:04:34,390 --> 00:04:35,000
has finished handling

81
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,190
the part regarding the foundation.

82
00:04:36,190 --> 00:04:38,600
Shall we schedule a meeting
with Mr. Wu Daonan?

83
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,680
Yes. You arrange it.

84
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:40,070
Got it.

85
00:04:40,070 --> 00:04:41,190
I'll be going then, Ms. Xia.

86
00:04:41,190 --> 00:04:41,600
Bye-bye.

87
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,130
Bye-bye.

88
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,000
Hello.

89
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,190
Can I help you?

90
00:04:52,070 --> 00:04:52,950
I...

91
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:54,830
I'm just looking around.

92
00:04:54,830 --> 00:04:56,830
I don't need any help. It's all good.

93
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,390
I see you've been coming here
quite often recently.

94
00:04:58,390 --> 00:04:59,880
Are you looking for someone?

95
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:00,480
No, no.

96
00:05:00,510 --> 00:05:01,240
I see

97
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:03,180
your windows are so clean.

98
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:03,950
You...

99
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:05,080
Nothing. It's okay.

100
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:09,950
You Li,

101
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:10,920
are you going to the hospital?

102
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,040
I'll give you a ride.

103
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:12,630
I-It's okay.

104
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:13,600
I can go by myself.

105
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:14,120
It's fine.

106
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,040
Let's go down together.

107
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,040
Come on. Let's go.

108
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:36,040
It's you again!

109
00:05:36,510 --> 00:05:38,310
I didn't bring a brick this time.

110
00:05:41,159 --> 00:05:42,270
When I got here,

111
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:43,870
she was sneaking around outside.

112
00:05:43,870 --> 00:05:45,270
Who was sneaking around?

113
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:48,120
I'm here to see my sister!
What's wrong with that?

114
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:49,310
You haven't gained any skills,

115
00:05:49,310 --> 00:05:50,830
but you've definitely become
more shameless.

116
00:05:50,830 --> 00:05:51,510
What's up?

117
00:05:51,830 --> 00:05:53,490
You want more cardboard? Huh?

118
00:05:53,830 --> 00:05:54,560
Xia Xiaolan,

119
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:55,560
you're cruel.

120
00:05:55,830 --> 00:05:57,070
You're capable of great deeds.

121
00:05:57,070 --> 00:05:58,750
You're amazing, having become a big boss!

122
00:05:58,750 --> 00:05:59,480
But you're my elder sister.

123
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,870
You won't even help your own sister.

124
00:06:00,870 --> 00:06:01,720
No matter what,

125
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,520
you're not a good person either.

126
00:06:06,610 --> 00:06:08,240
I don't care! You have to help me.

127
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,190
I don't care, anyway.

128
00:06:09,190 --> 00:06:10,800
I'm sticking around here! I'm...

129
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:11,560
I can't deal with this.

130
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,480
Let's go, Zhou Cheng.

131
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,040
Sister!

132
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:14,120
You can't leave.

133
00:06:16,270 --> 00:06:17,000
Xia Hongxia,

134
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,900
now you know to call me Sister?

135
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:21,650
If you want something, ask nicely.

136
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:23,560
Call me Sister sincerely,

137
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,000
and I'll consider it.

138
00:06:28,390 --> 00:06:28,870
Sister.

139
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,100
My dear sister.

140
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:37,480
I want you to help me find a job.

141
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:40,750
Aren't you working

142
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:41,610
for Ke Yixiong?

143
00:06:42,260 --> 00:06:43,680
That's not even a real job.

144
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:45,430
That work is inhuman!

145
00:06:46,630 --> 00:06:48,159
I know you look down on me.

146
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:50,560
The whole family looks down on me.

147
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,830
I have no skills, no brains.

148
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,920
I can't bring honor
to the family for Grandma.

149
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:56,240
But I'm not loafing around,

150
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,480
mooching off the family.

151
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:58,000
Why can't I

152
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,360
live a good life?

153
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:02,690
I'm fed up with their dirty looks.

154
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:05,030
I want to make a living with my own hands.

155
00:07:05,430 --> 00:07:06,560
I want to be like you.

156
00:07:08,660 --> 00:07:10,200
I want to be like you.

157
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:18,450
Alright.

158
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:19,450
Stop crying.

159
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:26,360
Which one do you think
I should let her work on?

160
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:28,560
Happy Life Materials, Luna, or Qi Hang?

161
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:29,510
Are you sure you'll

162
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:30,040
put her

163
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,430
somewhere related to you?

164
00:07:31,430 --> 00:07:32,890
You trust her that easily?

165
00:07:33,390 --> 00:07:35,120
If she genuinely wants to change,

166
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,980
she should start from the bottom.

167
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,360
Doesn't she have

168
00:07:38,510 --> 00:07:40,570
the experience working in an eatery?

169
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:41,560
I think

170
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,159
we might as well

171
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:43,240
let her return to her old trade,

172
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,440
selling box lunches.

173
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,630
It's also a way to see

174
00:07:45,630 --> 00:07:46,240
if she has really

175
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,370
figured things out.

176
00:07:48,390 --> 00:07:49,830
You're really considerate.

177
00:07:49,830 --> 00:07:51,920
It's indeed not bad
to have her sell box lunches.

178
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,380
At least she won't starve.

179
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:55,040
But where should she sell them?

180
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,430
A place that guarantees decent business

181
00:07:56,430 --> 00:07:57,310
and high foot traffic.

182
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,710
And customers can't be too picky
with food.

183
00:08:01,430 --> 00:08:02,510
Isn't there

184
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:04,890
already a place like that?

185
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:06,470
Right.

186
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:08,360
And we have acquaintances there.

187
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:09,070
You're so smart.

188
00:08:09,070 --> 00:08:09,670
Of course.

189
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:11,040
I'm home.

190
00:08:12,830 --> 00:08:13,600
I'm off then.

191
00:08:16,230 --> 00:08:16,760
Bye-bye.

192
00:08:17,070 --> 00:08:17,600
Bye-bye.

193
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,090
Here we are. This is it.

194
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,750
Yang and his family are

195
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:32,960
going back to their hometown.

196
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,750
So this stall is being transferred out.

197
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:35,840
Don't look down on this small stall.

198
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,900
The business is actually quite good.

199
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:39,390
Well... When I worked
at Ke Yixiong's place,

200
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:40,419
I was also a cook.

201
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:42,000
The job you found for me is

202
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,270
still the same.

203
00:08:44,910 --> 00:08:45,370
Well...

204
00:08:46,870 --> 00:08:47,720
Xia Hongxia,

205
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:48,390
right?

206
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:50,810
Take it or leave it.

207
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,390
If you don't like it,
just go back to Ke Yixiong's place.

208
00:08:53,390 --> 00:08:54,920
What kind of job do you want?

209
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:56,520
Do you know English?

210
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:58,370
Can you deal with clients?

211
00:08:58,440 --> 00:08:59,700
Can you sort out files?

212
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,750
Alright, stop provoking her.

213
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:03,270
Don't be

214
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:04,480
ungrateful.

215
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,960
That pittance Ke Yixiong paid you

216
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:08,760
wouldn't even cover your rent, right?

217
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:09,670
Xiaolan has already rented

218
00:09:09,670 --> 00:09:11,390
this stall for you.

219
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:13,080
From now on, you're the boss,

220
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,810
responsible for your own profits
and losses.

221
00:09:14,810 --> 00:09:15,720
You don't know how much better this is

222
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,180
than what we had back then.

223
00:09:18,510 --> 00:09:19,240
Xia Hongxia,

224
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:20,910
I see that you're still salvageable,

225
00:09:20,910 --> 00:09:22,370
so I want to lend you a hand.

226
00:09:22,510 --> 00:09:24,270
Back then, Sis Bai sold fruit.

227
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:26,910
And I also started
by selling duck eggs and oil cakes,

228
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:28,710
doing these dirty, tiring jobs.

229
00:09:28,790 --> 00:09:30,270
Our starting points are the same.

230
00:09:30,270 --> 00:09:31,360
But how far you can go

231
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,560
depends on yourself.

232
00:09:33,390 --> 00:09:34,670
Selling box lunches as a livelihood

233
00:09:34,670 --> 00:09:36,240
may not look glamorous,

234
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,910
but as long as you aren't greedy,

235
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:38,640
aren't lazy,

236
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,510
and don't want to be a parasite anymore,

237
00:09:40,510 --> 00:09:41,310
then at the very least,

238
00:09:41,310 --> 00:09:43,110
it guarantees you won't starve.

239
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,750
Although I don't understand

240
00:09:47,750 --> 00:09:49,320
the big principles you're talking about,

241
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,960
since even Xia Ziyu couldn't beat you,

242
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,760
you must be the more capable one.

243
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:53,870
So I'll listen to you.

244
00:09:53,870 --> 00:09:54,930
You can't be wrong.

245
00:09:56,270 --> 00:09:56,730
Sister,

246
00:09:56,980 --> 00:09:57,870
do you want to know something

247
00:09:57,870 --> 00:09:58,730
about my Uncle Dajun?

248
00:09:58,730 --> 00:09:59,860
I'm not interested.

249
00:10:00,790 --> 00:10:01,890
That stall is yours now.

250
00:10:01,890 --> 00:10:02,730
Go tidy it up.

251
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:25,740
Stop there!

252
00:10:28,550 --> 00:10:29,360
Tell me

253
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,080
why you quit

254
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,480
the job at Mr. Ke's place?

255
00:10:33,150 --> 00:10:35,610
Who will support you
if you don't earn money?

256
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:39,120
Your Uncle Dajun, that bastard,

257
00:10:39,150 --> 00:10:40,440
has been lured away

258
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:41,510
by that little vixen again

259
00:10:41,510 --> 00:10:43,480
and doesn't bring money home anymore.

260
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:43,960
Grandma!

261
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:45,670
How am I supposed to live?

262
00:10:45,790 --> 00:10:47,220
I didn't want to work there long ago!

263
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:47,910
Mr. Ke

264
00:10:47,930 --> 00:10:49,480
didn't treat me like a human at all.

265
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:50,790
I can find a job myself.

266
00:10:52,630 --> 00:10:53,270
I'll teach you a lesson!

267
00:10:53,270 --> 00:10:54,510
You hit me again!

268
00:10:54,870 --> 00:10:56,000
You can't control anyone now,

269
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,660
so you just keep hitting me, right?

270
00:10:57,660 --> 00:10:59,260
I know you all look down on me.

271
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:00,720
I have to rely on myself!

272
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:03,320
You...

273
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:08,110
How dare you!

274
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:09,360
You little wretch!

275
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:10,960
Stop crying.

276
00:11:11,550 --> 00:11:12,550
You're so noisy.

277
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:13,840
If you scare

278
00:11:13,870 --> 00:11:15,000
the baby in my belly,

279
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:17,120
see if Dajun will still support you.

280
00:11:17,630 --> 00:11:19,240
Or do you want to move out

281
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:21,290
with my brother-in-law's family?

282
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:27,670
You little... v-vixen.

283
00:11:27,690 --> 00:11:28,600
If I'm a vixen,

284
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,290
what does that make you?

285
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:31,720
And what about your grandson

286
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,120
in my belly?

287
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:35,530
Think carefully before you speak.

288
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:36,670
Fine.

289
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:38,240
Fine.

290
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:40,280
Just you wait.

291
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,240
Wait until my Dajun gets back.

292
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,840
I'll have him deal with you

293
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:46,330
-Seriously?
-and teach you a lesson!

294
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:47,550
Our family's life is

295
00:11:47,550 --> 00:11:48,410
getting worse,

296
00:11:48,630 --> 00:11:50,440
and it's at least half your fault.

297
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:52,270
You used to bully Liu Fen

298
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:54,000
and Xia Xiaolan all the time.

299
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:54,930
But they ended up

300
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:55,870
making it big.

301
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:57,870
Now you want to bully me.

302
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,930
Dajun fell for your trick once.

303
00:12:01,150 --> 00:12:01,750
You think he'll still

304
00:12:01,750 --> 00:12:03,080
listen to you this time?

305
00:12:05,150 --> 00:12:05,630
I...

306
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,030
I...

307
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:09,390
This is outrageous!

308
00:12:11,330 --> 00:12:13,170
[Majestic Mahjong]

309
00:12:13,910 --> 00:12:16,440
Why can't I get a match?

310
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:18,840
This is this month's income.

311
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,640
Just this little bit?

312
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:27,330
Keep playing. It's none of your business.

313
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:28,600
Boss.

314
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:31,720
Recently, several construction sites

315
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:34,150
switched to working with the Bai's fleet.

316
00:12:35,550 --> 00:12:36,630
Bai Zhenzhu led her team

317
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:38,630
to negotiate with them personally.

318
00:12:38,630 --> 00:12:40,270
The drivers are all fellow disciples

319
00:12:40,270 --> 00:12:41,440
from the Bai Martial Arts School.

320
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:43,150
They have real kung fu skills.

321
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,140
Besides, with Golden Sands Pool

322
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:47,670
endorsing their business,

323
00:12:47,790 --> 00:12:49,590
for those who are not close to us,

324
00:12:49,750 --> 00:12:50,750
Bai Zhenzhu could easily

325
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:51,750
snatch them away.

326
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:55,970
Business over the past 2 months
has obviously...

327
00:12:58,030 --> 00:12:59,270
But this mahjong parlor is actually

328
00:12:59,270 --> 00:13:00,870
doing pretty good business.

329
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:03,870
Mahjong parlor?

330
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:08,880
I work my fingers to the bone every day,

331
00:13:09,150 --> 00:13:11,080
yet I'm still stuck in this mahjong parlor

332
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,120
and make little money that's

333
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,920
not even enough to feed you guys!

334
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:14,840
Continue.

335
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,360
Xia Xiaolan, Bai Zhenzhu.

336
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:23,000
I didn't want to make enemies

337
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,630
of two women like you,

338
00:13:25,630 --> 00:13:27,320
but you forced my hand.

339
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:31,390
It was really not easy

340
00:13:31,390 --> 00:13:32,720
to invite you, Ms. Xia, to a meal.

341
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,750
You were either in Gangdao or Jiangcheng.

342
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:37,280
You weren't avoiding me on purpose,
were you?

343
00:13:37,940 --> 00:13:39,390
I haven't committed any crimes.

344
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:41,650
Why would I avoid you, Prosecutor Jiang?

345
00:13:43,630 --> 00:13:44,550
I'm very sorry

346
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,490
about what my mom did to you.

347
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:49,790
You don't need to apologize to me.

348
00:13:49,790 --> 00:13:50,390
I actually think

349
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:51,670
your mom's got a point.

350
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:53,000
During the fire,

351
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:53,510
your first reaction was

352
00:13:53,510 --> 00:13:54,870
to push Zhou Cheng away.

353
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,510
I should thank you.

354
00:13:58,910 --> 00:13:59,440
No matter who was

355
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:01,100
in the car with me at that time,

356
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:02,030
even if it were

357
00:14:02,030 --> 00:14:03,690
you, whom I'm not that fond of,

358
00:14:03,790 --> 00:14:04,910
I would've pushed you away.

359
00:14:04,910 --> 00:14:05,910
It's my instinct.

360
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:07,840
Of course, I also believe

361
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:08,790
that if you were in my shoes,

362
00:14:08,790 --> 00:14:11,050
you wouldn't have left me behind either.

363
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,670
Thank you for your honesty.

364
00:14:12,670 --> 00:14:15,000
And thank you
for thinking so highly of me.

365
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:20,870
Zhou Cheng and I

366
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,240
grew up together.

367
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:25,780
It's fair to call us
childhood sweethearts.

368
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:27,630
I do like Zhou Cheng.

369
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:29,630
There's no point in hiding it.

370
00:14:29,630 --> 00:14:31,090
I couldn't hide it anyway.

371
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:33,440
Just like the scars on my body.

372
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:36,870
Besides, as long as you are

373
00:14:36,870 --> 00:14:37,750
not married,

374
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,320
I still have a chance,

375
00:14:39,630 --> 00:14:40,120
don't I?

376
00:14:43,670 --> 00:14:44,840
I'm being this frank

377
00:14:45,150 --> 00:14:46,270
because I don't want things

378
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:47,670
to be awkward between us.

379
00:14:47,910 --> 00:14:48,720
Nor do I want it

380
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:49,910
to affect our work.

381
00:14:51,150 --> 00:14:52,270
Regarding the smuggling

382
00:14:52,270 --> 00:14:53,440
and these accidents,

383
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:55,440
I also want to get to the bottom of it.

384
00:14:57,270 --> 00:14:58,550
I actually don't really like

385
00:14:58,550 --> 00:14:59,810
having a rival in love.

386
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:01,980
But I appreciate your candor.

387
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,080
If...

388
00:15:13,250 --> 00:15:14,360
Just if...

389
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:16,600
If I hadn't

390
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,720
come to this world,

391
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:21,200
perhaps the story
between her and Zhou Cheng

392
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:23,200
would have turned out differently.

393
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:41,120
Mr. Wu, this way, please.

394
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:45,790
Mr. Wu,

395
00:15:45,910 --> 00:15:47,510
do you have any suggestions?

396
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:49,350
You've chosen a great location.

397
00:15:49,910 --> 00:15:51,640
With a pool right in the center.

398
00:15:51,790 --> 00:15:53,630
As long as the architecture
and environment are well-designed,

399
00:15:53,630 --> 00:15:54,630
it can't go wrong.

400
00:15:55,450 --> 00:15:57,270
Of course they're well-designed.

401
00:15:57,270 --> 00:15:58,320
After all, I graduated

402
00:15:58,320 --> 00:16:00,120
from Huaqing's Architecture School.

403
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:02,320
And we have Mr. Mao
overseeing the project.

404
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:02,960
Ms. Xia,

405
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:06,630
could we use my consultation fee

406
00:16:06,870 --> 00:16:07,600
as a discount

407
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:09,480
on an apartment in the Golden Sands Pool?

408
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:10,550
That would be wonderful.

409
00:16:10,550 --> 00:16:12,080
Having you move in, Mr. Wu, would be

410
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:12,810
the best advertisement

411
00:16:12,810 --> 00:16:14,270
for the Golden Sands Pool.

412
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:17,630
This place has pleasant scenery

413
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:19,870
as well as high-end facilities nearby.

414
00:16:19,870 --> 00:16:21,720
It's not as bustling as Gangdao.

415
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,750
It really is a great place to live.

416
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:26,750
However, I have

417
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:28,530
a personal suggestion.

418
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:32,970
Replace this pile of rebar with sand.

419
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,560
Stacking it like this

420
00:16:34,710 --> 00:16:36,350
during construction

421
00:16:36,540 --> 00:16:38,140
can easily cause accidents.

422
00:16:41,790 --> 00:16:42,850
How's this outfit?

423
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:43,850
Looks great.

424
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:44,870
Will I be cold?

425
00:16:44,870 --> 00:16:46,730
Should I change into another one?

426
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:48,150
Xiaolan,

427
00:16:48,270 --> 00:16:49,510
we're almost late.

428
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:50,980
Okay, fine.

429
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:51,740
Let's go.

430
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:52,840
Okay, let's go.

431
00:16:58,670 --> 00:16:59,130
Hold on.

432
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,510
I forgot the present for Zhenzhu.

433
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:01,240
Xiaolan,

434
00:17:01,550 --> 00:17:02,610
come here for a sec.

435
00:17:03,030 --> 00:17:03,480
Okay.

436
00:17:03,670 --> 00:17:04,329
Can you go get it?

437
00:17:04,329 --> 00:17:05,750
It's in that bag on the table.

438
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:06,109
Sure.

439
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,210
Come on, Wei!

440
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:14,880
Go for it, Wei!

441
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:15,940
Do you need my help?

442
00:17:16,069 --> 00:17:17,880
You can't even beat one of his hands
with two of yours.

443
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:18,400
Let me help you.

444
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:18,750
Okay?

445
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:20,440
Don't talk. I'm trying my best here.

446
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:21,030
Sis Bai.

447
00:17:21,210 --> 00:17:21,680
Zhenzhu.

448
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:22,089
Welcome.

449
00:17:22,089 --> 00:17:23,020
Happy Birthday.

450
00:17:23,349 --> 00:17:24,440
Wei, the audacity!

451
00:17:24,690 --> 00:17:25,680
You can't even beat Sis Bai
at arm wrestling,

452
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:26,680
and you're trying to take on San?

453
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:28,590
There's no shame in losing to San.

454
00:17:28,590 --> 00:17:29,000
I...

455
00:17:30,030 --> 00:17:31,830
I bought you a birthday cake.

456
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:33,720
I told you,

457
00:17:33,750 --> 00:17:35,210
I don't do that fancy Western stuff.

458
00:17:35,210 --> 00:17:36,250
I ordered longevity noodles.

459
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:37,200
They'll be served soon.

460
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,480
No way, it's a birthday.

461
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:39,680
You must have a cake.

462
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:43,880
You know what, Sis Bai?

463
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:45,080
This is the trend now.

464
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:46,400
Just go with the flow.

465
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:47,750
Come on, blow out the candles.

466
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:48,210
Sis Bai,

467
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:50,070
this is a birthday present for you.

468
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:50,790
Thank you.

469
00:17:50,790 --> 00:17:51,640
I'll open it later.

470
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:52,070
Okay.

471
00:17:53,590 --> 00:17:53,960
Good.

472
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:58,590
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

473
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:02,000
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

474
00:18:02,310 --> 00:18:05,920
♪ Happy birthday to me (you) ♪

475
00:18:08,110 --> 00:18:12,510
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

476
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:19,480
Ms. Bai,

477
00:18:19,920 --> 00:18:22,450
I finished singing
the birthday song for you.

478
00:18:22,790 --> 00:18:23,350
So,

479
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:26,220
aren't you going to cut me
a slice of cake?

480
00:18:28,070 --> 00:18:29,440
Mr. Ke.

481
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:31,270
What?

482
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:34,440
You couldn't win fair and square,

483
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:36,100
so you came here to talk trash?

484
00:18:36,830 --> 00:18:38,830
Ms. Bai, are you saying

485
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:41,440
that you won't show me, Ke, any respect?

486
00:18:41,530 --> 00:18:42,610
My Bai's fleet

487
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:44,720
relies on our own skills to make a living.

488
00:18:44,720 --> 00:18:46,380
Why should I show you respect?

489
00:18:50,350 --> 00:18:51,000
Your men

490
00:18:51,030 --> 00:18:52,740
can't stop their shady business.

491
00:18:52,740 --> 00:18:54,800
Is it my fault that you lost your turf?

492
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:57,720
Listen.

493
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:00,310
Be it the business pie

494
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:02,440
or today's birthday cake,

495
00:19:04,870 --> 00:19:06,600
I won't share any of it with you.

496
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:15,240
Guys.

497
00:19:15,550 --> 00:19:16,070
Yes.

498
00:19:16,350 --> 00:19:17,310
Didn't we

499
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:19,400
prepare a gift for Ms. Bai?

500
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:22,660
Bring out the big gift!

501
00:19:40,830 --> 00:19:41,480
Stop!

502
00:19:57,440 --> 00:19:58,840
Do you want to keep going?

503
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:12,240
You're all pretty tough.

504
00:20:14,510 --> 00:20:15,440
Since

505
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:17,170
Ms. Bai and Ms. Xia

506
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,460
won't show me respect,

507
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:21,160
let's settle it in business.

508
00:20:30,550 --> 00:20:32,270
Tastes good. Nice cake.

509
00:20:33,270 --> 00:20:33,960
Let's go!

510
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:44,970
Are you okay?

511
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:49,030
Xiaolan, are you alright?

512
00:20:49,030 --> 00:20:49,560
I'm fine.

513
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:52,550
That jerk.

514
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:54,750
He ruined

515
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,010
my nice birthday cake.

516
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,440
It's okay, Sis Bai.

517
00:20:58,590 --> 00:20:59,200
Didn't you just say

518
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:00,750
there's still a bowl of longevity noodles?

519
00:21:00,750 --> 00:21:01,590
As for the cake,

520
00:21:01,590 --> 00:21:03,320
I'll buy you another one, okay?

521
00:21:05,030 --> 00:21:06,510
But after the scene

522
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:07,980
Ke Yixiong made today,

523
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:09,750
you and San must be careful.

524
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:10,590
from now on.

525
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:12,160
Don't worry, Xiaolan.

526
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:12,890
With me here,

527
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:13,530
Ke Yixiong

528
00:21:13,560 --> 00:21:15,090
wouldn't dare do anything.

529
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:16,750
Alright, alright.

530
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:17,830
Let's eat up.

531
00:21:17,830 --> 00:21:18,560
I'm so hungry

532
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:20,070
and running out of energy.

533
00:21:20,070 --> 00:21:21,070
Yes, let's dig in.

534
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:35,800
Xiaolan.

535
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:40,180
Has anything happened

536
00:21:40,830 --> 00:21:41,630
to you lately?

537
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:44,090
What do you mean?

538
00:21:47,790 --> 00:21:48,840
I just noticed you

539
00:21:50,270 --> 00:21:51,200
zoning out a lot,

540
00:21:52,270 --> 00:21:54,070
looking distracted sometimes.

541
00:21:55,350 --> 00:21:56,480
What's on your mind?

542
00:21:59,480 --> 00:22:01,880
Maybe I've just been
swamped with work lately.

543
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:02,480
I...

544
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:05,920
I don't even know myself

545
00:22:06,110 --> 00:22:07,510
what I'm thinking about.

546
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:09,960
Just now,

547
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:12,030
I didn't even recognize

548
00:22:12,030 --> 00:22:13,090
who Ke Yixiong was.

549
00:22:31,510 --> 00:22:32,240
What is this?

550
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:38,690
Xiaolan.

551
00:23:40,590 --> 00:23:42,120
First, I owe you an apology.

552
00:23:43,270 --> 00:23:45,070
I looked through this notebook.

553
00:23:45,550 --> 00:23:46,200
But I honestly couldn't

554
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,600
understand the content.

555
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:49,640
These strings of numbers

556
00:23:50,030 --> 00:23:51,350
look like dates.

557
00:23:52,350 --> 00:23:53,550
But if they are dates,

558
00:23:54,750 --> 00:23:57,040
there are still plenty of inconsistencies.

559
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:58,480
Like "1983-8-15,"

560
00:23:58,510 --> 00:23:59,910
that's obviously a date.

561
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:02,350
But as for "New Year's Day, 2026,"

562
00:24:02,350 --> 00:24:03,550
if that's also a date,

563
00:24:04,070 --> 00:24:06,000
that's more than 30 years from now.

564
00:24:07,960 --> 00:24:08,490
Xiaolan,

565
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:12,160
are you hiding something?

566
00:24:13,510 --> 00:24:14,200
Something

567
00:24:14,830 --> 00:24:15,960
I can't understand,

568
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:17,590
or something I

569
00:24:18,240 --> 00:24:19,350
can't accept?

570
00:24:20,480 --> 00:24:21,240
Like

571
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:24,080
you're from another planet,

572
00:24:24,350 --> 00:24:25,070
or...

573
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,360
you're from the future?

574
00:24:43,510 --> 00:24:44,200
Yes.

575
00:24:47,880 --> 00:24:49,010
I'm from the future.

576
